<br><br>

<h4>Risks</h4>
<p>A major risk about creating a new product and application is that it might not take off, all the funding and time spent might all be wasted if the product doesn&apost have consumers. Some of the language to code for the application may be learnt slower than others and this might slow down the progress of developing the application and the functions. The documentation between the group might be hard to understand or might not even exist, this can affect the progress of the development too. Another risk could be the ability to transfer documents, the uncertainty that someone might intercept the documents or that some members are unable to send through documents due to their internet restrictions. A major risk would consist of our adaptor being inadequate to grant access for &quotnon-smart&quot devices to connect with the Wi-Fi making it a smart device. The Raspberry Pi or similar products might be difficult to understand or achieve our desired goal.</p>
<br><br>

<h4>Group Processes and Communications</h4>
<p>Telkom+ group mostly record conversations formally in Microsoft Teams, but, informal conversations are held in Facebook messenger or discord. We tend to pin messages that are important so that we can access the message easily. As mentioned in the group process, full Telkom+ group member meetings take place 3 times a week, in addition to that, there would be an extra of 1 meeting to discuss the urgent matters, not all group members could attend but we record the meeting for those who missed the meeting.</p>
<p>Fortunately, Telkom+ group members are easily contactable, and with that, we had no issue about non-responding group members in our team. But, if such a case happens, we will try to direct message the member or call through facebook messenger and call them a number of times. If the member is still ignoring the messages and calls, on behalf of the group, group leader will have to take action on emailing Dr. B, and reflect the group member's behavious in SparkPLUS.</p>
<br><br>

<h4>Skills and Jobs</h4>
<p><u>Software Engineer</u></p>
<p>Completed an undergraduate degree such as a Bachelor of Computer Science or a Bachelor of Software Engineering. Proficient knowledge in one or more coding languages including Java, Python or C++. 3-5 year of experience in working in this field. Ability to work independently and cooperatively in a team environment. </p>
<p><u>User Interface Designer</u></p>
<p>Completed an undergraduate degree such as Bachelor of Design (Web Design, Graphic Design) or a Diploma of Graphic Design. 3-5 year of experience in this field. Proficient use of Adobe photoshop, wireframing or UI design tools. Looking for someone with a creative mindset and someone who is self-motivated. Ability to work independently and cooperatively in a team environment. </p>
<p><u>Programmer</u></p>
<p>Completed an undergraduate degree such as a Bachelor of Computer Science, Bachelor of Information Technology, or a Diploma of Software development. A minimum of 3 years of experience in this field. Proficient knowledge in coding languages such as Python or C++. Ability to work independently and cooperatively in a team environment. </p>
<p><u>Testing Analyst</u></p>
<p>Completed an undergraduate degree such as a Bachelor of Computer Science or Bachelor of Information Technology. Minimum of 2 year of experience in this field. Proficient use of Microsoft Office applications including Word, Excel, Visio, and PowerPoint. Ability to work independently and cooperatively in a team environment.</p>
